chars we replace the chars that are same in\\n// both the string with one so that if we find the same char ahead in the /// string we dont stop at the current index and where it was present \\n\\n\\n//   EG ---> aabaaaaa\\n//    1st iteration --->1abaaaaa\\n//     2nd iteration ----> 11baaaaa\\n\\n            magazine = magazine.replace(item,\\"1\\");\\n\\n            count ++; // in count we count the no of times we\'ve entered the if condition \\n        }\\n        \\n    }\\n\\n\\n// we now check if the count === length of ransomeNote that means \\n// that many times the condition was true and magazine consists of every \\n// char that ransomeNote has\\n\\n\\n        if(count === len1)\\n        {\\n            return true ;\\n        }\\n        else\\n        {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n\\n\\n        IF you liked the explaination do upvote please Thanks\\n};","compare_result":null,"title_slug":"ransom-note","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1,"frontend_id":11},{"id":929691284,"question_id":908,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"3\xc2\xa0years, 2\xc2\xa0months","timestamp":1680882681,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"0 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/929691284/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Middle of the Linked List","memory":"40.8 MB","code":"/**\\n * Definition for singly-linked list.\\n * public class ListNode {\\n *     int val;\\n *     ListNode next;\\n *     ListNode() {}\\n *     ListNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\\n *     ListNode(int val, ListNode next) { this.val = val; this.next = next; }\\n * }\\n */\\nclass Solution {\\n    public ListNode middleNode(ListNode head) {\\n        if(head==null)\\n            return null;\\n        ListNode slow=head;\\n        ListNode fast=head;\\n        while(fast!=null && fast.next!=null) {\\n            slow=slow.next;\\n            fast=fast.next.next;\\n        }\\n        \\n        return slow;\\n        \\n    }\\n}","compare_result":"11111111111111111111111111